title.narrative: IR1 - ESSENTIAL HEALTH SERVICES

description.narrative: IR 1: Increased proportion of women and children receiving quality evidence-based essential integrated maternal and child care services by December 2013, which contributes to Care And Treatment Of Children Affected By Hiv And Aids, Child Health, Hiv Prevention, Hygiene, Immunization, Infant And Young Child Feeding, Maternal And Newborn Health, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Sanitation, Treatment And Care Of Children Living With Hiv, Water Supply. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: UNICEF will contribute to increasing number of women and children have equitable Access to and Use of Quality Essential Social and Protection Services and practices with fon vulnerable groups and the most marginalised regions of Kenya by 2013
